article.headline: Lipscomb 75, Fla Atlantic 67
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Albert Hacker scored 22 points and Brian Fisk added 16 points and 14 rebounds as Lipscomb beat Florida Atlantic 75-67 Thursday night. Florida Atlantic (8-12, 5-8 Atlantic Sun Conference) sent the Bisons to the free throw line 12 times in the final minute, with Lipscomb hitting seven before Fisk stole an inbound pass for a layup at the buzzer. Florida Atlantic pulled within three points at 46-43 with 11:10 to play on a Mike Bell basket. The Owls would get no closer the rest of the game. A slow start left Lipscomb (7-14, 4-8) trailing 30-29 at the half, but the Bisons gained momentum after the break by scoring on its first two possessions. Hacker put up most of his numbers in the second half, scoring 16 points, grabbing all eight of his rebounds and topping it off with eight blocked shots. Bell scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds for Florida Atlantic. Robert Williams added 14 points.
